  "records": {
    "description": "A handful of compact, 1-wide tileable (1wt) falling edge detectors, which are redstone circuits designed to output a brief pulse when an input signal transitions from on to off.",
    "features": [
      "1-wide design for space efficiency",
      "Tileable, allowing multiple units to be placed side-by-side",
      "Detects falling edges in redstone signals, useful for timing and automation"
    ],
    "considerations": [
      "Requires understanding of redstone mechanics",
      "Some designs may vary in speed or reliability based on components used"
    ],
    "notes": "These are commonly used in Minecraft redstone engineering for creating precise timing circuits.",
    "compatibility": "Compatible with Minecraft Java Edition versions 1.11 and later (where observers are available); similar concepts work in Bedrock Edition with adjustments.",
    "instructions": [
      "One simple design: Place an observer facing the input signal.",
      "Connect the observer's output to a repeater or comparator to create the pulse.",
      "For a piston-based version: Use a sticky piston with a block and redstone torch to detect the edge.",
      "Test the circuit to ensure it triggers only on falling edges."
    ]
